  {
    "Id": "CFG_040",
    "Name": "Use Memory Grant Feedback (Batch and Row Mode) to Optimize Query Resource Allocation",
    "Description": "Memory Grant Feedback is an advanced Intelligent Query Processing (IQP) feature that dynamically adjusts the amount of memory allocated to a query based on its actual historical usage. This mechanism significantly improves resource efficiency by reducing \"over-grants\" (wasted system memory) and preventing performance bottlenecks caused by \"under-grants,\" which force data spills to slower temporary storage (tempdb).\nProper configuration is crucial for optimizing complex, high-volume workloads in modern SQL Server versions, ensuring stable query execution and optimal resource utilization.",
