  {
    "Id": "CFG_048",
    "Name": "Ensure Automatic Seeding is Enabled for Availability Groups (AGs)",
    "Description": "Automatic seeding is a critical feature for maintaining high availability (HA) and disaster recovery (DR) readiness in SQL Server Availability Groups (AGs). This check validates that automatic seeding is enabled, which significantly automates the initial data synchronization process when adding new secondary replicas. By eliminating the need for manual backup and restore steps, it minimizes human error, reduces operational complexity, and ensures faster, more reliable database provisioning across all replicas. However, administrators must also be aware of best practices regarding Very Large Databases (VLDBs), which may require careful consideration or manual seeding despite automatic seeding being enabled.|",
