    "Description": "The presence of duplicate indexes on identical key columns is a significant performance anti-pattern. These redundant indexes consume excessive storage space, memory resources, and critically increase I/O overhead during data modification operations (INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE). Furthermore, they can confuse the SQL Server Query Optimizer, potentially leading to suboptimal execution plans or plan variability, thereby degrading overall database performance. Best practice mandates that only necessary and non-redundant indexes should be maintained on a table.",
