  {
    "Id": "CFG_254",
    "Name": "Handling of Referential Integrity Constraints During Bulk Loading",
    "Description": "This check validates the procedure for handling data integrity constraints (such as Foreign Keys, CHECK constraints, and UNIQUE constraints) during high-volume bulk data loading operations. While temporarily disabling these constraints can significantly boost write performance by avoiding real-time validation overhead, this practice bypasses critical data quality rules. If this technique is used, robust compensating controls must be implemented to ensure the loaded data adheres to all necessary business logic and referential integrity requirements post-load.",
    "Category": "Configuration",
