    "Description": "This check validates that the SQL Server Max Degree of Parallelism (MAXDOP) is configured appropriately for the underlying hardware architecture. MAXDOP limits the maximum number of processors a query can use in a parallel plan, directly impacting performance and resource utilization across all workloads. Incorrect settings—such as setting it too high relative to the CPU core count or NUMA nodes, or leaving it at the default value on modern systems—can lead to severe performance degradation, inefficient resource scheduling, or even denial-of-service conditions for critical applications. Best practice dictates aligning this setting with the physical hardware capabilities (e.g., setting it to 0 or a specific core count) as recommended by Microsoft and CIS benchmarks.",
