  {
    "Id": "GEN_056",
    "Name": "Set min server memory to adhere to best practices",
    "Description": "This check validates the configuration of the minimum server memory setting (min server memory). This option defines a guaranteed lower bound for the amount of RAM SQL Server will attempt to keep allocated. While setting this value prevents potential resource starvation in highly constrained or multi-instance virtualized environments, Microsoft's current best practice recommends leaving this setting at 0 MB. Setting it incorrectly can lead to severe memory pressure issues or prevent SQL Server from starting properly.",
