    "Name": "Configure Automated Backup Preference on Secondary Replica to Offload Primary Load",
    "Description": "This check validates that the automated backup preference for an Always On Availability Group (AG) is configured to direct backups away from the primary replica. Performing routine database backups, especially full or log backups, on the primary replica can generate significant I/O and CPU load, potentially degrading production query performance and availability. By utilizing a designated secondary replica as the preferred target for automated backups, system resources are offloaded, ensuring continuous optimal performance for critical workloads while maintaining robust data protection capabilities.",
